      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COOL AND CLASSY (1) drew wide and worked against the boys last time so will relish both the ace draw and the return to her own sex. Had kicked off the campaign with back-to-back wins. Classy mare who can take full advantage of the barrier and prove very hard to catch. RUBY RULES (3) beat COOL AND CLASSY home when midfield from the back row last week. Had finished top-three in her other three starts this time in including an easy win from the second line at Albion Park. Looks the danger. PLATINUM JEWEL (7) draws to get a nice trail behind Cool And Classy and goes very well at this circuit and distance with two wins and a placing from three attempts. SHEZ SWEET LOUISE NZ (6) draws wide for her return but has won three of four fresh attempts so include along with CHANGE TACT NZ (8) who is going well enough to be competitive with even luck.",
